---
import { noWorriesCaseStudyImages } from '../../data/noWorriesCaseStudy';
import { aboutContactIcons } from '../../data/aboutAssets';
import { contactEmail, socialLinks } from '../../data/aboutContent';

const images = noWorriesCaseStudyImages;

const backToChapterHref = '/?highlight=no-worries#chapter-1';
---

<article class="scarlett-case-study">
  <header class="scarlett-case-study__hero">
    <p class="scarlett-case-study__project-name">No Worries</p>
    <h1 class="scarlett-case-study__hero-title">
      A concept-driven board game that makes the hidden costs of everyday <strong>social expression</strong> visible and playable.
    </h1>
  </header>

  <section class="scarlett-case-study__section" aria-labelledby="no-worries-inspiration">
    <p id="no-worries-inspiration" class="scarlett-case-study__section-label">DESIGN INQUIRY</p>

    <div class="scarlett-case-study__copy scarlett-case-study__copy--inspiration no-worries-case-study__inquiry">
      <h2 class="scarlett-case-study__block-title">
        Between Harmony and Self
      </h2>
      <p class="scarlett-case-study__body no-worries-case-study__inquiry-lead">
        The project began with my own difficulty in expressing personal needs while trying to remain polite, considerate, and socially acceptable.
      </p>

      <div class="scarlett-case-study__inspiration-row scarlett-case-study__inspiration-row--tension">
        <div class="no-worries-case-study__inquiry-follow">
          <p class="scarlett-case-study__body">
            This tension became the central design inquiry:
          </p>
          <p class="scarlett-case-study__body">
            <strong>How might the hidden personal and relational costs of everyday expression become visible, discussable, and playable?</strong>
          </p>
        </div>

        <div
          class="no-worries-case-study__tension"
          role="group"
          aria-label="Caught between maintaining harmony and protecting the self"
        >
          <div class="no-worries-case-study__tension-panel">
            <p class="no-worries-case-study__tension-title">Maintain Harmony</p>
            <ul class="no-worries-case-study__tension-list">
              <li>Avoid conflict or discomfort</li>
              <li>Suppress personal needs</li>
              <li>Quieter voices overlooked</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="no-worries-case-study__tension-center">
            <svg
              class="no-worries-case-study__tension-icon"
              viewBox="0 0 48 48"
              width="48"
              height="48"
              aria-hidden="true"
              focusable="false"
            >
              <circle cx="24" cy="12" r="7.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.25" />
              <path
                d="M9 41.5c0-9.5 6.7-15.5 15-15.5s15 6 15 15.5"
                fill="none"
                stroke="currentColor"
                stroke-width="2.25"
                stroke-linecap="round"
              />
            </svg>
            <p class="no-worries-case-study__tension-caption">Caught between both</p>
          </div>

          <div class="no-worries-case-study__tension-panel">
            <p class="no-worries-case-study__tension-title">Protect Self</p>
            <ul class="no-worries-case-study__tension-list">
              <li>Direct expression</li>
              <li>Protect own needs</li>
              <li>May create pressure</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="scarlett-case-study__section" aria-labelledby="no-worries-game-design">
    <p id="no-worries-game-design" class="scarlett-case-study__section-label">RESEARCH FRAMING</p>

    <div class="scarlett-case-study__stack">
      <div class="scarlett-case-study__text-block">
        <h2 class="scarlett-case-study__block-title">
          Expression as a Contextual Trade-off
        </h2>
        <p class="scarlett-case-study__body">
          The research reframed expression as neither simply direct nor indirect, but as a contextual balance between personal needs, emotional effort, social comfort, and relationships.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="no-worries-case-study__framing-split">
        <div class="no-worries-case-study__framing-copy">
          <div class="no-worries-case-study__framing-points">
            <div class="scarlett-case-study__rule-copy">
              <p class="scarlett-case-study__rule-title">Maintaining harmony has a cost</p>
              <p class="scarlett-case-study__rule-body">Adapting to others may protect short-term comfort while gradually reducing Self or Energy.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="scarlett-case-study__rule-copy">
              <p class="scarlett-case-study__rule-title">Directness is not always the answer</p>
              <p class="scarlett-case-study__rule-body">Both soft and direct expression can support or damage relationships depending on context.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="scarlett-case-study__rule-copy">
              <p class="scarlett-case-study__rule-title">Personality shapes social pressure</p>
              <p class="scarlett-case-study__rule-body">The same expression may require different levels of effort from different people.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="scarlett-case-study__copy scarlett-case-study__copy--inspiration">
            <h2 class="scarlett-case-study__block-title">
              Translating experience into a system
            </h2>
            <p class="scarlett-case-study__body">
              Rather than representing communication through dialogue alone, I translated invisible social pressure into cards, tokens, costs, and group-level changes.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="no-worries-case-study__framing-table-wrap">
          <table class="no-worries-case-study__mapping-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th scope="col">Experience</th>
                <th scope="col">Game Mechanism</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td>Difficulty saying no</td>
                <td>Expression Cards</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Social pressure</td>
                <td>Scene Cards</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Emotional effort</td>
                <td>Energy</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Suppressed needs</td>
                <td>Self</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Maintaining harmony</td>
                <td>Face</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Shared responsibility</td>
                <td>Cooperation and Task Progress</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="scarlett-case-study__section" aria-labelledby="no-worries-game-development">
    <p id="no-worries-game-development" class="scarlett-case-study__section-label">
      SYSTEM DESIGN
    </p>

    <div class="scarlett-case-study__text-block">
      <h2 class="scarlett-case-study__block-title">
        Social Expression as Negotiation
      </h2>
      <div class="double-vision-case-study__narrative-arc-act-block">
          <p class="scarlett-case-study__rule-title">Personality</p>
          <p class="scarlett-case-study__rule-body">Defines each player’s social tendency, strengths, and pressures.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="double-vision-case-study__narrative-arc-act-block">
          <p class="scarlett-case-study__rule-title">Expression</p>
          <p class="scarlett-case-study__rule-body">Players choose how to support, refuse, soften, delay, confront, or repair.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="double-vision-case-study__narrative-arc-act-block">
          <p class="scarlett-case-study__rule-title">Personal State</p>
          <p class="scarlett-case-study__rule-body">Each expression affects Self, Face, and Energy.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="double-vision-case-study__narrative-arc-act-block">
          <p class="scarlett-case-study__rule-title">Social Space</p>
          <p class="scarlett-case-study__rule-body">Individual choices reshape group tension, task progress, and relationships.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="scarlett-case-study__text-block">
      <h2 class="scarlett-case-study__block-title">
        Context Changes Meaning
      </h2>
      <p class="scarlett-case-study__body">
        The Context Translator represents the distance between what someone intends to express and how others interpret it.
      </p>
      <p class="scarlett-case-study__body">
        It combines the current situation, personality, expression, and social state to reveal possible outcomes such as support, misunderstanding, over-commitment, or hidden tension.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="scarlett-case-study__section" aria-labelledby="no-worries-reflection">
    <p id="no-worries-reflection" class="scarlett-case-study__section-label">REFLECTION</p>

    <div class="scarlett-case-study__text-block">
      <h2 class="scarlett-case-study__block-title">A Model for Reflection, Not Diagnosis</h2>
      <p class="scarlett-case-study__body">
        No Worries succeeds in making pressure, compromise, and self-suppression tangible, but it remains a simplified model of complex human behaviour.
      </p>
      <p class="scarlett-case-study__body">
        The project is not intended to identify personality types or teach a correct communication style. Its purpose is to create a space where different forms of expression and their consequences can be experienced and discussed.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="scarlett-case-study__subsection">
      <p class="scarlett-case-study__subsection-label">FINAL POSTER</p>
      <p class="scarlett-case-study__body">
        The final poster summarises the concept, system, components, and design process in one visual overview.
      </p>

      <figure class="no-worries-case-study__poster">
        <img
          class="no-worries-case-study__poster-img"
          src={images.designPoster}
          alt="No Worries final design poster"
          loading="lazy"
          decoding="async"
        />
      </figure>
    </div>
  </section>


  <footer class="scarlett-case-study__footer">
    <a class="scarlett-case-study__back" href={backToChapterHref}>← Back to Chapter</a>

    <div class="scarlett-case-study__closing">
      <p class="scarlett-case-study__thanks">
        Thank you for exploring my world! If it resonates, I'd love to hear from you.
      </p>
      <div class="scarlett-case-study__credit">
        <span class="scarlett-case-study__name">Hang Wan</span>
        <span class="scarlett-case-study__credit-dot" aria-hidden="true">·</span>
        <span class="scarlett-case-study__role">Design Playful Experience</span>
        <span class="scarlett-case-study__credit-divider" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <div class="scarlett-case-study__credit-links">
          <a
            class="scarlett-case-study__credit-link"
            href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}
            aria-label="Email Hang Wan"
          >
            <img
              class="scarlett-case-study__credit-icon"
              src={aboutContactIcons.gmail}
              alt=""
              width="44"
              height="44"
              loading="lazy"
            />
          </a>
          <a
            class="scarlett-case-study__credit-link"
            href={socialLinks.linkedin}
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            aria-label="LinkedIn"
          >
            <img
              class="scarlett-case-study__credit-icon"
              src={aboutContactIcons.linkedin}
              alt=""
              width="44"
              height="44"
              loading="lazy"
            />
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </footer>
</article>

<script>
  function initCaseStudyMedia() {
    document.querySelectorAll('[data-case-study-img]').forEach((img) => {
      if (!(img instanceof HTMLImageElement) || img.dataset.mediaBound === 'true') return;
      img.dataset.mediaBound = 'true';

      const markMissing = () => {
        const figure = img.closest('[data-case-study-media]');
        figure?.classList.add('is-missing');
      };

      img.addEventListener('error', markMissing);
      if (img.complete && img.naturalWidth === 0) markMissing();
    });

    document.querySelectorAll('[data-case-study-video]').forEach((video) => {
      if (!(video instanceof HTMLVideoElement) || video.dataset.mediaBound === 'true') return;
      video.dataset.mediaBound = 'true';

      const markMissing = () => {
        const figure = video.closest('[data-case-study-media]');
        figure?.classList.add('is-missing');
      };

      video.addEventListener('error', markMissing);
    });
  }

  initCaseStudyMedia();
  document.addEventListener('astro:page-load', initCaseStudyMedia);
</script>
